canonical:
  title: 晉陽公追薦疏
  author: 河千旦
  language: lzh
  text: 聞佛誕於右脥說恩重經以遐傳曰文擔於左肩繞須彌山而難報念無用之弱質早失容於嚴顔早年未盡其誠孝曷勝哀慕祥旦俄臨於今日庶助淸昇伻趍寶刹以演眞仍掃私廬而作法伏願迴觀平日所信向之空門斗斷妄緣直徑登於覺地
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 晉陽公追薦疏
  author: 河千旦
  language: lzh
  text: 聞佛誕於右脥。說恩重經以遐傳。曰文擔於左肩。繞須彌山而難報。念無用之弱質。早失容於嚴顔。早年未盡其誠孝。曷勝哀慕。祥旦俄臨於今日。庶助淸昇。伻趍寶刹以演眞。仍掃私廬而作法。伏願迴觀平日。所信向之空門。斗斷妄緣。直徑登於覺地。
korean:
  title: 진양공을 추하여 천도하는 글
  author: 하천단
  language: kor
  text: 듣건대 부처님은 오른 옆구리로부터 탄생하셨기에 《은중경(恩重經)》을 말씀하여 널리 전하기를 “왼 어깨에 아버지를 업고 수미산(須彌山)을 돌아도 은혜 갚기 어렵다.” 하셨나이다. 생각하건대, 제자는 쓸데 없는 약한 자질로써 일찍 아버지를 여의었으므로, 젊을 때 그 효성 다하지 못했음을 애모(哀慕)하던 나머지, 오늘의 상서로운 아침에 다달아 혹시 청승(淸昇)을 돕고자 하여 먼저 보찰(寶刹)에 나아가 진전(眞詮)을 연출[演]하고 이내 사려(私廬)에 돌아와 법회를 일으키나이다.원하건대, 평소의 신심을 관찰하여 빨리 공문(空門)에 나아가게 하며, 망령된 인연을 끊고 바로 깨닫는 자리에 오르게 하옵소서.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1140_010_0240&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001] 文 : '
    value: 父
english:
  title: A Memorial Prayer for the Ascension of Lord Jinyang
  author: Ha Cheon-dan
  language: eng
  text: |-
    I have heard that the Buddha was born from his right side, and thus he proclaimed the Sutra of Profound Gratitude, teaching that "though one carries one's father upon the left shoulder and circles Mount Sumeru, it remains difficult to repay such debt."

    I reflect upon my own weakness and unworthiness—having lost my father in youth, I failed to fulfill my filial duty in those early years. How can I bear such longing and regret? Yet as this auspicious day arrives, I humbly offer what assistance I can toward his elevation to the pure realms. First, I journey to the sacred temple to expound the true teachings, then return to my humble dwelling to conduct this dharma service.

    I earnestly beseech: may you observe the faith held in ordinary days and swiftly enter through the gate of emptiness; may you sever the bonds of delusion and ascend directly to the seat of enlightenment.
  footnotes:
    - 'Mount Sumeru (須彌山): In Buddhist cosmology, the central mountain of the universe, representing the axis of spiritual elevation'
    - 'The Sutra of Profound Gratitude (恩重經): A Buddhist text emphasizing the immeasurable debt owed to parents, often cited in East Asian funeral and memorial rites'
    - This piece appears to be a memorial prayer composed for a father's funeral or posthumous Buddhist ceremony, blending Confucian filial piety with Buddhist practice
